sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant IT as IT Ops

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    S->>F: Credit check request
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION — Added risk assessment with expedited path for low-risk customers
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Credit Score, Company Status, Payment History)
    alt Low-Risk (Score >750 AND Verified Company AND Clean Payment History)
        F-->>S: Auto-Approved – Low Risk (Expedited Path)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited)
    else High-Risk
        F->>F: Escalate to Finance Director
        F-->>S: Finance Director Approval (24h SLA)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts
    end
    %% END CHANGED SECTION
    IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Replaced the single Finance approval step with a risk assessment decision point using an `alt/else` block. The low-risk path (credit score >750, verified company status, no payment history issues) auto-approves and proceeds directly to expedited account provisioning, bypassing Finance Director review. High-risk customers are escalated to the Finance Director for approval under the existing 24h SLA before provisioning proceeds. Both paths then converge at the welcome email step.